<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,906,1973]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,480,1026,1052]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Diagnostic characters:</emphasis>
The species can be separated from the two other members of the genus by the absence of spines on the third palpomere, wing cells and veins bare, the shape of the lateral lamellae of the virga, and the low inferior volsella.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,906,1973]" box="[197,1379,1146,1173]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,342,1146,1172]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Etymology:</emphasis>
From Latin 
<emphasis box="[489,588,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">confusio</emphasis>
, meaning confusion, as it superficially looks like an 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saether" authorityYear="1981" box="[1207,1371,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Antillocladius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1207,1371,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Antillocladius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,906,1973]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,260,1186,1212]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Male</emphasis>
(n = 1). Total length 2.16 mm. Wing length 1.24 mm. Total length / wing length 1.73. Wing length / length of profemur 2.67. Coloration dark brown, thorax dark brown without distinct marks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,906,1973]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[197,268,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Head.</emphasis>
AR 1.28. Ultimate flagellomere 
<quantity box="[654,745,1267,1293]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.46" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="446.0">446 µm</quantity>
long. Temporal setae 9, including 4 inner verticals, 3 outer verticals, and 2 postorbitals. Clypeus with 3 setae. Tentorium, stipes, and cibarial pump as in 
<figureCitation box="[1253,1370,1307,1333]" captionStart="FIGURES 79–83" captionStartId="57.[151,269,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[237,1346,239,1734]" captionTargetId="figure-69@57.[188,1398,194,1782]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 79–83. Litocladius confusus sp. n., male. 79—tentorium, stipes, and cibarial pump; 80—thorax; 81—wing; 82—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 83—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, dorsal aspect to the left and ventral aspect to the right." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133938/files/figure.png" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Figure 79</figureCitation>
. Tentorium 
<quantity box="[236,327,1347,1373]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0699999999999998" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="107.0">107 µm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[400,477,1347,1373]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 µm</quantity>
wide. Stipes 
<quantity box="[633,724,1347,1373]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.04" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="104.0">104 µm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[797,874,1347,1373]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="45.0">45 µm</quantity>
wide. Palp segment lengths (in µm): 18, 48, 68, 59, 82. Third palpomere with 3 sensilla clavata subapically, longest 
<quantity box="[947,1023,1387,1413]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 µm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,906,1973]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[197,282,1427,1452]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[297,384,1427,1453]" captionStart="FIGURES 79–83" captionStartId="57.[151,269,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[237,1346,239,1734]" captionTargetId="figure-69@57.[188,1398,194,1782]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 79–83. Litocladius confusus sp. n., male. 79—tentorium, stipes, and cibarial pump; 80—thorax; 81—wing; 82—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 83—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, dorsal aspect to the left and ventral aspect to the right." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133938/files/figure.png" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
). Antepronotum with 2 setae. Dorsocentrals 8; acrostichals composed of at least 4 anterior strong decumbent setae, 2 weak simple, and 5 posterior scalpellate setae; prealars 3; supraalar 1. Scutellum with 4 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,906,1973]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[197,257,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[274,362,1547,1573]" captionStart="FIGURES 79–83" captionStartId="57.[151,269,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[237,1346,239,1734]" captionTargetId="figure-69@57.[188,1398,194,1782]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 79–83. Litocladius confusus sp. n., male. 79—tentorium, stipes, and cibarial pump; 80—thorax; 81—wing; 82—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 83—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, dorsal aspect to the left and ventral aspect to the right." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133938/files/figure.png" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
). VR 1.37. C extension 
<quantity box="[649,726,1547,1573]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="36.0">36 µm</quantity>
long. Brachiolum with 1 seta, veins and cells bare. Squama with 11 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,906,1973]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[197,260,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Legs.</emphasis>
Spur of foretibia 
<quantity box="[474,552,1627,1653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="43.0">43 µm</quantity>
long, spurs of midtibia 
<quantity box="[839,918,1627,1653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 µm</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[977,1055,1627,1653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 µm</quantity>
long, spurs of hind tibia 
<quantity box="[1358,1436,1627,1653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="39.0">39 µm</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[203,281,1667,1693]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 µm</quantity>
long. Width at apex of foretibia 
<quantity box="[679,760,1667,1693]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="27.0">27 µm</quantity>
, of midtibia 
<quantity box="[916,997,1667,1693]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 µm</quantity>
, of hind tibia 
<quantity box="[1168,1250,1667,1693]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="29.0">29 µm</quantity>
. Comb with 13 setae, longest 
<quantity box="[316,394,1707,1733]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="27.0">27 µm</quantity>
, shortest 
<quantity box="[505,581,1707,1733]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 µm</quantity>
long. Lengths and proportions of legs as in 
<tableCitation box="[1096,1200,1707,1733]" captionStart="TABLE 13" captionStartId="58.[151,239,151,175]" captionText="TABLE 13. Lengths (in µm) and proportions of legs of Litocladius confusus sp. n., male (n = 1)." pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Table 13</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,906,1973]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[197,347,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[363,502,1747,1773]" captionStart="FIGURES 79–83" captionStartId="57.[151,269,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[237,1346,239,1734]" captionTargetId="figure-69@57.[188,1398,194,1782]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 79–83. Litocladius confusus sp. n., male. 79—tentorium, stipes, and cibarial pump; 80—thorax; 81—wing; 82—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 83—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, dorsal aspect to the left and ventral aspect to the right." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133938/files/figure.png" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Figs 82–83</figureCitation>
). Tergite IX covered with strong microtrichia, laterosternite IX with 6–7 setae. Anal point narrowly triangular, 
<quantity box="[524,601,1787,1813]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="59.0">59 µm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[675,752,1787,1813]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="38.0">38 µm</quantity>
wide at base, 
<quantity box="[920,982,1787,1813]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 µm</quantity>
wide at apex, with 22 setae. Phallapodeme 
<quantity box="[222,300,1827,1853]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="75.0">75 µm</quantity>
long, transverse sternapodeme 
<quantity box="[672,749,1827,1853]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="73.0">73 µm</quantity>
long. Virga 
<quantity box="[897,974,1827,1853]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="39.0">39 µm</quantity>
long. Gonocoxite 
<quantity box="[1194,1286,1827,1853]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.34" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="134.0">134 µm</quantity>
long. Gonostylus 
<quantity box="[226,303,1867,1893]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="64.0">64 µm</quantity>
long, megaseta 
<quantity box="[493,555,1867,1893]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 µm</quantity>
long. HR 2.11, HV 3.38.
</paragraph>
